 * @param {Object}   [userConfig] User's custom config 
 * @param {String}   [userConfig.model.jsonPath = ''] Path to Live2D model's main json eg. `https://test.com/miku.model.json` model
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.model.scale = 1] Scale between the model and the canvas canvas
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.model.hHeadPos = 0.5] Horizontal position of model's head 
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.model.vHeadPos = 0.618] Vertical position of model's head 
 * @param {Array}    [userConfig.model.myDefine = []] User's custom Defines which will override LDefine LDefine
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.display.superSample = 2] rate for super sampling rate 
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.display.width = 150] Width to the canvas which shows the model canvas
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.display.height = 300] Height to the canvas which shows the model canvas
 * @param {String}   [userConfig.display.position = 'right'] Left of right side to show 
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.display.hOffset = 0] Horizontal offset of the canvas canvas
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.display.vOffset = -20] Vertical offset of the canvas canvas
 * @param {Boolean}  [userConfig.mobile.show = true] Whether to show on mobile device 
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.mobile.scale = 0.5] Scale on mobile device 
 * @param {Boolean}  [userConfig.mobile.motion = true] Whether to enable motion detection on mobile devices 
 * @param {String}   [userConfig.name.canvas = 'live2dcanvas'] ID name of the canvas canvasID
 * @param {String}   [userConfig.name.div = 'live2d-widget'] ID name of the div divID
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.react.opacityDefault = 0.7] Default opacity 
 * @param {Number}   [userConfig.react.opacityOnHover = 0.2] OnHover opacity 
 * @param {Function} [userConfig.react.myFunc = func(e)] Custom event handler, won't override main handler, will reveice the event type. 
 * @param {Boolean}  [userConfig.dev.log = false] Whether to show log 
 * @param {Boolean}  [userConfig.dev.border = false] Whether to show border around the canvas canvas
 * @param {Boolean}  [userConfig.dev.mouseLog = false] Whether to show mouse log (tons of log), only work when dev.log is enabled 
 * @param {Function} [userConfig.dev.mouseFunc = func(x, y, ix, iy)] Custom logger, only work when dev.log is enabled, will receive (x, y, ix, iy), which presents the actucally position and vitural position 
 * @return {null}
